Jack Alexander of the popular musical act The Alexander Brothers has died at the age of 77.

The Scottish folk legend, who performed across the world with his brother Tom, died peacefully at 1.40pm yesterday surrounded by his family, according to an official statement.

He was being treated at Ayrshire Hospice in Ayr after suffering a massive stroke last month.

