The brothers, originally from Cambusnethan in Wishaw, Lanarkshire, were among Scotland's best-loved entertainers.

They performed to fans around the world for more than 50 years.

In the 1950s, they started performing on stage in a series of talent contests across central Scotland.

Jack was an accomplished piano player, while 79-year-old Tom favoured the accordion.

They won every competition they entered between 1950 and 1956, according to their fan club biography.

The duo then decided to play professionally - taking to the stage at Webster Theatre in Arbroath in 1958.

